message:
Thanks for answer.

But I'm writing my own impementation of MVC 5 Identity, so I need to implement ie:  
> public virtual Task<string> GetEmailAsync(TUser user)

but email field is just in TUser, so I'm writing   
> return Task.FromResult<string>(user.Email);

so simplified method is :   
public virtual Task<string> GetEmailAsync(TUser user) {  
 // add .ConfigureAwait(false) to returned task ???  
 return Task.FromResult<string>(user.Email);   
}

So, add .ConfigureAwait(false) to such Task.FromResult<string> or not add ? :-)

